  "label": "Rift-Vigil Dormitory Cell",
  "description": "Rift-Vigil Dormitory Cell is a narrow sleeping chamber cut into the temple’s basalt interior, its walls ribbed with slagcrete buttressing to resist the ash-laden gales beyond. A low stone cot and recessed storage niches are built directly into the masonry, minimizing loose furnishings in the electrostatic environment. Copper grounding strips run along the floor margins, tying the room into the temple’s latticed discharge system. Auroraglass vents admit thin bands of bruise-colored light that fall across soot-dark surfaces in hard, unwavering lines.",
